    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <p> at length arrived <persName ref="pe0157">Mr Macgovanâ€™s</persName> parcel for
                    which the poor engraver &amp; I are much obliged to you.</p>
                <p>I am vastly pleased with y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> booksellers. printing
                    these little old tracts; I assure you I will puff them off.</p>
                <p>Doctor Webster is most obliging. if he will be so good as to draw up a concise
                    account of his excellent plan. It will be a great obligation.<note type="editorial">Possibly a reference to the Church of Scotland Minister
                            <persName ref="pe0085">Alexander Webster</persName>, author of <bibl type="editorial">
                            <title ref="bi0589">
                                <hi rend="italic">An account of the
                                    number of people in Scotland in the year one thousand seven
                                    hundred and fifty-five</hi>
                            </title> (1755)</bibl>.</note> I have
                            <bibl type="authorial">
                        <title ref="bi0075">the acts of parlement</title>
                    </bibl> but do
                    not understand the affair well enough to do it. I beg my best compliments though
                    unknown to him.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>I am D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Sir in much haste y<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>
                    </salute>
                    <signed>
                        <persName ref="pe0232">T Pennant</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <dateline>Nov<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> 12<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>
                    1773.</dateline>
            </div>
            <div>
                <p>
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Paton</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>at the Custom house</addrLine>
                    </address>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
